@page "/"

<PageTitle>EasyWoWMacro - World of Warcraft Macro Editor & Validator</PageTitle>

<div class="container-fluid">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-12">
            <div class="jumbotron text-center py-5">
                <h1 class="display-4">EasyWoWMacro</h1>
                <p class="lead">Create and validate World of Warcraft macros with real-time syntax checking</p>
                <hr class="my-4">
                <p>Build macros with conditionals, validate syntax, and get instant feedback. Designed for WoW players who want reliable, error-free macros.</p>
                <a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" href="macro-editor" role="button">Open Editor</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row mt-4">
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <div class="card h-100">
                <div class="card-body text-center">
                    <i class="bi bi-check-circle text-success" style="font-size: 2.5rem;"></i>
                    <h5 class="card-title mt-3">Syntax Validation</h5>
                    <p class="card-text">Real-time validation of macro syntax, commands, and conditionals. Catch errors before using macros in-game.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <div class="card h-100">
                <div class="card-body text-center">
                    <i class="bi bi-eye text-info" style="font-size: 2.5rem;"></i>
                    <h5 class="card-title mt-3">Structure Analysis</h5>
                    <p class="card-text">Visual breakdown of macro components - directives, commands, conditionals, and arguments for better understanding.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <div class="card h-100">
                <div class="card-body text-center">
                    <i class="bi bi-clipboard text-warning" style="font-size: 2.5rem;"></i>
                    <h5 class="card-title mt-3">Easy Export</h5>
                    <p class="card-text">Copy validated macros directly to clipboard. Character limit validation ensures compatibility with WoW's macro system.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row mt-4">
        <div class="col-12">
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-header">
                    <h4>Example Macro</h4>
                </div>
                <div class="card-body">
                    <p>Here's an example of a macro that the editor can parse and validate:</p>
                    <pre class="bg-light p-3 rounded"><code>#showtooltip
/cast [@@target,harm,nodead] Smite; [@@target,help,nodead] Flash Heal
/use [combat] Healthstone
/say [combat] Using Healthstone!</code></pre>
                    <p class="mt-3">This macro demonstrates conditionals for different target types, combat-based item usage, and chat commands. The validator checks each component for proper syntax.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row mt-4">
        <div class="col-12">
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-header">
                    <h4>About WoW Macros</h4>
                </div>
                <div class="card-body">
                    <p>World of Warcraft macros allow players to automate actions and create custom spell rotations. With EasyWoWMacro, you can:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Create conditional macros</strong> that adapt to different situations (combat, target type, modifiers)</li>
                        <li><strong>Validate syntax</strong> before using macros in-game</li>
                        <li><strong>Understand macro structure</strong> through visual breakdown</li>
                        <li><strong>Stay within character limits</strong> with real-time counting</li>
                        <li><strong>Use advanced conditionals</strong> like @@target, @@mouseover, mod:shift, and more</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>Whether you're creating mouseover macros for healing, optimizing DPS rotations, or setting up defensive cooldowns, EasyWoWMacro helps you build reliable macros efficiently.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
